raw_data.title: Professional Consultant II
raw_data.description: Under the supervision of others can perform the tasks and functions described above, as well as, more difficult and complex activities. raw_data.title: Senior Professional Consultant I
raw_data.description: Performs the tasks and functions described above, as well as, complex work under the oversight of others. raw_data.title: Facilitator I
raw_data.description: Responsible for all aspects of performance (e.g., technical, contractual, administrative, financial). Consults with the customer to ensure conformity to contractual obligations, establishes and maintains technical and financial reports to show progress of projects to management and customers, organizes and assigns responsibilities to subordinates, oversees and manages the successful completion of all assigned tasks. With oversight may direct the work of others and/or act in the role of Project Manager, Lead Instructor, or Subject Matter Expert.

raw_data.title: Project Specialist I
raw_data.description: Includes business and financial personnel performing functions duties such as contract management, project control, finance and accounting, project planning and scheduling, and cost estimating. Typical duties include assist in strategic planning by analyzing financial reports, human resources, operational processes performing accounting, program management, financial reporting and/or program control functions, and reporting to a manager or team leader for directions.

raw_data.title: Business Specialist I
raw_data.description: Includes business and financial personnel performing functions such as contract management, project control, finance and accounting, project planning and scheduling, and cost estimating. Typical duties include developing program  management  and analytical tools for tracking and reporting; providing financial  and business advice, support and guidance to technical  managers; evaluating, developing and implementing procedures, processes, techniques, models, and/or systems required to effectively manage programs; developing and maintaining relationships with customers, subcontractors, consultants and vendors to facilitate successful program performance and problem resolution; and providing daily supervision and direction to assigned staff.

raw_data.title: Subject Matter Expert I
raw_data.description: Expertise in the specific industry or subject matter expertise within a specified discipline. Typical duties include provide highly specialized guidance and in-depth experience and knowledge in technical issues, as well as analysing complex project. Acting as consultant and advisor to senior managers, professional staff, and policy makers.  Participate in discussions, provide evaluation and advice to policies, along with support and guidance in technical research and provide problem resolution and maintain current knowledge of relevant technology as assigned and ensures accuracy of project deliverables.
